    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10114497>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Setostylus xoxo spec. nov. Holotype male. A. Antenna, lateral view (dorsal edge on right). B. Thorax, dorsal view. C–E. Legs, lateral view. C. Fore leg. D. Mid leg. E. Hind leg. Abbreviations: cx = coxa; fe = femur; flgm 1 = first flagellomere; hlt = halter; pe = pedicel; tb = tibia; tb spr = tibial spur; tr = trochanter; tsm 1 = tarsomere 1; scp = scape. Scale: A= 0.1 mm; B–E= 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10114497/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10114499>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Setostylus xoxo spec. nov. Holotype male. Wing, dorsal view. Abbreviations: C = costal vein; CuA = anterior branch of cubital veins; CuP = posterior branch of cubital veins; h = humeral crossvein; m-cu = medial cubital crossvein; R+M fus = radial + medial fusion; M1, M2 and M4 = branches of medial vein; R1, R2+3, R4+5 = radial veins; Rs = radial sector; Sc = subcostal vein. Scale= 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10114499/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10114501>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Setostylus xoxo spec. nov. Holotype male. A. Abdomen, ventral view. B, D. Male genitalia, ventral view. C, E. Tergite 9, dorsal view (posterior edge at top in the Fig. E). Scales:A = 0.5 mm; B–C = 0.1 mm; D–E = 0.16 mm. Abbreviations: Ae com= Aedeagal complex; cer = cerci; gs = gonostylus; gx = gonocoxites; pa = paramere." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10114501/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10114503>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Setostylus xoxo spec. nov. Distribution (solid circles) in states of Morelos, Mexico and Arizona, USA." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10114503/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

